  "text": "Equation (10) is the fundamental model in this paper. It has three important characteristic worthy of indicating explicitly. at first, the energy distribution of clutter and target buried in it on spatial-frequency plane could be obtained by solving linear equation (10) of unknown x and known r which is spatialtemporal sample data. In other words, operation of STAP is essentially a process of solving linear algebraic equation from our point of view. Secondly, the row dimension N ×L of matrix Φ is much less than column dimension N s ×N d typically. Hence equation (10) is heavily ill-posed. The number of unknown variables is much more than the number of equations. That is to say, there are infinite vectors satisfying [CITATION_1] in general and some constraint should be imposed to help us to get some solution with unique feature. Thirdly, from viewpoint of STAP, the solution of (10) we are searching for is \"Sparse\". More rigorously, most of its entry are negligible and only a small portion of elements in solution vector, which represents contribution of main clutter and target, are remarkable, just as description in standard textbook of STAP [CITATION_2] [CITATION_3] . This kind of \"Sparsity\" is the basis of application of sparse recovery technique on STAP. Before our new approach is proposed, some necessary background of sparse processing will be sketched briefly.",
